    "summary": "I am interested in situations at work nobody wants to be in, but which are inevitable in everyday workplaces - the intricacies of bad news delivery.\n\nI am a postdoctoral researcher at the University of Groningen, NL, at the Dpt. of Organizational Psychology. I obtained my Phd in social sciences and economics at the University of Klagenfurt, Dept. of Organizations, Human Resources, and Service Management. My Bachelor's and Master's degrees are in psychology, with specializations in work- and organizational psychology and clinical psychology. Besides my scholarly pathway, I have working experience in the semiconductor industry (automotive) and on the federal level in designing suicide- and depression prevention strategies. \n\nIn my research, I am passionate to create practical impact through enhancing the effectiveness of bad news delivery that alleviates challenges for senders and recipients. I am also involved in research projects devoted to enhancing rigor in quantitative research methods or examining individual and organizational determinants of resilience in leaders. \nI am a lecturer on Human Resource Management for management students, a lecturer in Research Practicum for psychology students, and supervise Bachelor and Master theses in Human Resources and Organizational Behavior broadly.\n\nTo recharge, I am passionately training a Beagle to be a search dog.",
